java -mx8g -cp "*" edu.stanford.nlp.pipeline.StanfordCoreNLPServer -port 9000



-Xms8m      Selects a low initial JVM heap size for an application.
-cp         ClassPath option
edu.stanford.nlp.pipeline.StanfordCoreNLPServer     Package Name
-port       Option



desc:
Xms8m = initialize a memory loction (JVM Heap)
with classpath - giving the class path to *
then we are specifying the package name

and passing the -port option and port value for the program



































